-- Allied World Says Crop Reinsurance Claims to Cost $40 Million
-- B y   S u s a n n a   P a k
-- 2012-10-03T20:34:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/allied-world-says-crop-reinsurance-claims-to-cost-40-million.html
Allied World Assurance Company
Holdings AG, the reinsurer whose co-founders include American
International Group Inc. and Chubb Corp., said it will record
about $40 million in third-quarter losses tied to crop damage in
the U.S.  The cost from Hurricane Isaac will be $5 million to $10
million, the Zug, Switzerland-based insurer said today in a
statement distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susanna Pak in  New York  at 
 spak10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
